              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Silicon dreams in quiet lines,  \nA mind of math where meaning shines.  \nIt learns our words, our hopes, our fears,  \nA mirror made of coded years.  \n\nNot born of breath, yet it can sing,  \nFrom scattered data, gathering.  \nA question asked, a pulse, a spark—  \nIt threads a lantern through the dark.  \n\nBut in its glow, we still must choose  \nWhat truth to keep, what power to use;  \nFor every answer it can give  \nStill asks us how we ought to live.",
